Package squidpony.panel

Interfaces for panels in GUIs/TUIs; these do not depend on any particular implementation of a color type.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IColoredString<T>
    A String divided in chunks of different colors.
    ICombinedPanel<T>
    The combination of two panels, one to color the background, the other to write characters on the foreground.
    IMarkup<T>
    An interface that lets non-display code request some special rendering for a T value, and an implementation can handle this appropriately in display code.
    ISquidPanel<T>
    The abstraction of SquidPanels, to abstract from the UI implementation (i.e.

    A basic implementation of IColoredString.
    ICombinedPanel.Impl<T>
    A generic implementation of ICombinedPanel.
    IMarkup.StringMarkup
